Understanding the CRD Structure

1. Metadata Section

	name: Must follow the format <plural>.<group>
	group: Your organization's domain (avoid conflicts)

2. Spec Section

	group: API group for your resources
	scope: Namespaced or Cluster
	names: Different name formats for the resource
	versions: API versioning support

3. Schema Validation

	openAPIV3Schema: Validates incoming resources
	required: Mandatory fields
	enum: Allowed values
	pattern: Regex validation
	minimum/maximum: Numeric constraints

4. Status Subresource

	Typically managed by controllers
	Represents current state
	Separate from desired state (spec)
